        <li>
          <div class="collapsible-header active">Single Rate Commission</div>
          <div class="collapsible-body">
            <p>This is the standard commission that a realtor receives. The commission will be split by the buying and selling agents, but it is negotiated on the selling side. This is an easy to understand option that is never a bad choice, but we do recommend tiered or flat fee commissions over it.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="collapsible-header">Flat Fee</div>
          <div class="collapsible-body">
            <p>This is the fee that you will pay to your realtor regardless of the sales price of your home. If you have an easy to sell home or you do not want to pay the (often) larger fees associated with a commission, then this is probably the right option for you.</p>
